.TH "WK" "1" "Jan 01, 1980" "0.3.1" "wk"
.SH NAME
wk \- Which-Key via X11 and Wayland
.sp
wk is a popup menu for your custom keyboard shortcuts.
Inspired by
\X'tty: link https://github.com/justbur/emacs-which-key'\fI\%emacs\-which\-key\fP\X'tty: link',
\X'tty: link https://tools.suckless.org/dmenu/'\fI\%dmenu\fP\X'tty: link', and
\X'tty: link https://github.com/Cloudef/bemenu'\fI\%bemenu\fP\X'tty: link'\&.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.sp
\fBwk\fP [options]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.sp
\fBwk\fP provides visual feedback when executing user defined key chords via a popup
menu. The key chords may be precompiled into \fBwk\fP for users who maintain their
own copy of \fBwk\fP\&. For users looking for a more dynamic experience, \fBwk\fP can read
key chords from a \fI\%wks\fP file or script.
.SH OPTIONS
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
\fB\-h, \-\-help\fP
Display help message and exit.
.TP
\fB\-v, \-\-version\fP
Display version number and exit.
.TP
\fB\-d, \-\-debug\fP
Print debug information during execution.
.TP
\fB\-D, \-\-delay\fP \fIINT\fP
Delay the popup menu by \fIINT\fP milliseconds from startup or last keypress
(default 1000 ms).
.TP
\fB\-\-keep\-delay\fP \fIINT\fP
Delay in milliseconds after keyboard ungrab before command execution for
+keep chords. Helps prevent focus\-stealing issues with compositor commands
(default 75 ms).
.TP
\fB\-t, \-\-top\fP
Position menu at top of screen.
.TP
\fB\-b, \-\-bottom\fP
Position menu at bottom of screen.
.TP
\fB\-s, \-\-script\fP
Read \fBwks\fP script from stdin to use as key chords.
.TP
\fB\-U, \-\-unsorted\fP
Disable sorting of key chords (sorted by default).
.TP
\fB\-m, \-\-max\-columns\fP \fIINT\fP
Set the maximum menu columns to \fIINT\fP (default 5).
.TP
\fB\-p, \-\-press\fP \fIKEY(s)\fP
Press \fIKEY(s)\fP before dispalying menu. See \fI\%Trigger Key\fP
in the \fBwks\fP man page for more info.
.TP
\fB\-T, \-\-transpile\fP \fIFILE\fP
Transpile \fIFILE\fP to valid \(aqkey_chords.h\(aq syntax and print to stdout.
.TP
\fB\-k, \-\-key\-chords\fP \fIFILE\fP
Use \fIFILE\fP for key chords rather than those precompiled.
.TP
\fB\-w, \-\-menu\-width\fP \fIINT\fP
Set menu width to \fIINT\fP\&. Set to \(aq\-1\(aq for a width equal to 1/2 of the
screen width (default \-1).
.TP
\fB\-g, \-\-menu\-gap\fP \fIINT\fP
Set menu gap between top/bottom of screen to \fIINT\fP\&. Set to \(aq\-1\(aq for a gap
equal to 1/10th of the screen height (default \-1).
.TP
\fB\-\-wrap\-cmd\fP \fISTRING\fP
Wrap all chord commands by executing them as \fI/bin/sh \-c \(dqSTRING CMD\(dq\fP
where CMD is the original command. This does not apply to hooks (default \(dq\(dq).
.TP
\fB\-\-border\-width\fP \fIINT\fP
Set border width to \fIINT\fP (default 4).
.TP
\fB\-\-border\-radius\fP \fINUM\fP
Set border radius to \fINUM\fP degrees. 0 means no curve (default 0).
.TP
\fB\-\-wpadding\fP \fIINT\fP
Set left and right padding around hint text to \fIINT\fP (default 6).
.TP
\fB\-\-hpadding\fP \fIINT\fP
Set up and down padding around hint text to \fIINT\fP\&. (default 2)
.TP
\fB\-\-table\-padding\fP \fIINT\fP
Set additional padding between the outermost cells and the border to
\fIINT\fP\&. \-1 = same as cell padding, 0 = no additional padding (default \-1).
.TP
\fB\-\-fg\fP \fICOLOR\fP
Set all menu foreground text to \fICOLOR\fP where color is some hex string
i.e. \(aq#F1CD39\(aq (default unset).
.TP
\fB\-\-fg\-key\fP \fICOLOR\fP
Set foreground key to COLOR (default \(aq#DCD7BA\(aq).
.TP
\fB\-\-fg\-delimiter\fP \fICOLOR\fP
Set foreground delimiter to COLOR (default \(aq#525259\(aq).
.TP
\fB\-\-fg\-prefix\fP \fICOLOR\fP
Set foreground prefix to COLOR (default \(aq#AF9FC9\(aq).
.TP
\fB\-\-fg\-chord\fP \fICOLOR\fP
Set foreground chord to COLOR (default \(aq#DCD7BA\(aq).
.TP
\fB\-\-fg\-title\fP \fICOLOR\fP
Set foreground title to COLOR (default \(aq#DCD7BA\(aq).
.TP
\fB\-\-fg\-goto\fP \fICOLOR\fP
Set foreground goto to COLOR (default \(aq#E6C384\(aq).
.TP
\fB\-\-title\fP \fISTRING\fP
Set global title displayed above menu to STRING.
.TP
\fB\-\-title\-font\fP \fISTRING\fP
Set title font to STRING. Should be a valid Pango font description
(default \(aqsans\-serif, 16\(aq).
.TP
\fB\-\-bg\fP \fICOLOR\fP
Set background to COLOR (default \(aq#181616\(aq).
.TP
\fB\-\-bd\fP \fICOLOR\fP
Set border to COLOR (default \(aq#7FB4CA\(aq).
.TP
\fB\-\-shell\fP \fISTRING\fP
Set shell to STRING (default \(aq/bin/sh\(aq).
.TP
\fB\-\-font\fP \fISTRING\fP
Set font to STRING. Should be a valid Pango font description
(default \(aqmonospace, 14\(aq).
.TP
\fB\-\-implicit\-keys\fP \fISTRING\fP
Set implicit keys to STRING (default \(aqasdfghjkl;\(aq).
.UNINDENT
.SH BUG REPORTS
.sp
If you find a bug in \fBwk\fP, please report it at https://github.com/3L0C/wk.
